Create Locally Hosted Bookmark Sync with Nextcloud and Floccus
Setting Up Nextcloud
Log into Nextcloud
Click the gear icon in the upper right corner > Click Apps
Press CTRL + F and search bookmark
Find the Bookmarks app and click the Download and Enable button
Setting Up Floccus
In Firefox or a Chromium based browser, install the Floccus add-on or extension
In Brave Browser, open a new tab and navigate to https://chrome.google.com/webstore/category/extensions
Search for Floccus
Click on floccus bookmarks sync
Click the Add to Brave button > Click Add Extension to confirm
Click the hamburger menu > Extensions
Find floccus bookmarks sync and click the Details button
Scroll down and click Extension options
Click the New Account button
Select Nextcloud Bookmarks > Click the Add Account button
Enter the Nextcloud URL, username and password
Expand the Folder mapping section
Under Local folder, click the folder icon to browse the current browser's bookmark locations
Select Bookmarks > Click the Save button
Click the Save button
Add a bookmark in the browser to test the sync
Click the Extensions button > floccus bookmarks sync
Click the Sync Now button
The test bookmark should sync to Nextcloud
After the initial sync, floccus will automatically sync bi-directionally every 15 minutes by default. This interval can be configured in the extension options
